Subject: Re: [T2] Electronic module in distributor

On Mon, Feb 09, 2004 at 09:32:48AM -0800, Courtney Hook wrote:
> I've installed my electronix module into my distributor and have
> noticed that the point where the collar goes by the pickup on the
> module is quite different from where the camlobe would have opened
> the points. Am I correct in assuming that my distributor is going to
> be turned a similar amount of the difference to create the same
> timing? Thanks,

It shouldn't matter at all. Since you have to time an electronic
points system dynamically w/ a light you will simply adjust the
distributor body to whatever it needs to be. As long as you get 4
pulses for the plugs at every 2 revs of the crank all is fine.

